        "content": "<p>Hi everyone, I have a newbie question about polynomials.<br>\nSuppose we have </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">variables</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">field</span> <span class=\"n\">K</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">field</span> <span class=\"n\">L</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">algebra</span> <span class=\"n\">K</span> <span class=\"n\">L</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">p</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">polynomial</span> <span class=\"n\">K</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>How should I get the canonical  image of <code>p</code> in <code>polynomial L</code>? (or the canonical map  <code>polynomial K â†’  polynomial L</code> itself)  It seems that there is no <code>has_coe</code> instance for this already written down.</p>",
